&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Company Description&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Workleap is a Montreal-based tech company, founded in 2006. We&#39;re builders at heart, we make simple products that actually matter to the people who use them. We have two product lines:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://workleap.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Workleap Agent&lt;/a&gt;, our agentic HR platform that helps managers become better leaders, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://sharegate.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;ShareGate&lt;/a&gt;, the world&#39;s leading solution for Microsoft 365 migration and governance. More than 15,000 companies worldwide trust us to do exactly that. We&#39;re intentional about who joins us. If you&#39;re the kind of person who gets excited by a hard problem and wants to help shape what comes next, there&#39;s a place for you here.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Your role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Workleap&#39;s engineering organization is at an inflection point. We have two ambitious product lines, teams that ship, and a real window to change how we build. What&#39;s needed now is someone who can move engineering from a support function to a true velocity engine — more autonomous, more AI-enabled, and capable of delivering end-to-end value without the dependencies that slow everyone down. As Head of Technology, reporting directly to the CPTO &amp;amp; Co-Founder, you&#39;ll lead the Shared Tech group (~20 people), spanning Product Ops, Data, and Security &amp;amp; Infrastructure — the foundation on which both product lines run. Your mandate: stabilize, clarify, and accelerate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your impact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;12598&quot; data-local-id=&quot;0d7e25952609&quot;&gt;Increase engineering velocity and impact by enabling teams to ship end-to-end value with minimal dependencies;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;12712&quot; data-local-id=&quot;8906928997ec&quot;&gt;Improve delivery performance through stronger deployment frequency, shorter lead times, and sustained production reliability;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;12841&quot; data-local-id=&quot;966aa0d64a45&quot;&gt;Reduce organizational friction by increasing team autonomy, simplifying workflows, and clarifying ownership;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;12953&quot; data-local-id=&quot;c4fc20d6783c&quot;&gt;Accelerate delivery cycles and reduce manual effort through AI and automation embedded across development workflows;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;13073&quot; data-local-id=&quot;3dfcc1497d14&quot;&gt;Increase the leverage of product teams through scalable platform capabilities across Product Operations, Data, and Security &amp;amp; Infrastructure;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;13218&quot; data-local-id=&quot;630ebe762c01&quot;&gt;Strengthen accountability by aligning teams around production outcomes, customer impact, and end-to-end ownership;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;13336&quot; data-local-id=&quot;44da4fae7478&quot;&gt;Elevate organizational performance by building strong technical leadership and high-performing teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Over the next 6 to 12 months, your mandate is clear: transform engineering into a faster, more autonomous, and more reliable delivery engine. Concretely, that means enabling end-to-end delivery with fewer dependencies, embedding AI and automation across the full development lifecycle, strengthening engineering systems and platform foundations to durably increase impact per builder, and reinforcing ownership and accountability across teams.&lt;/p&gt;
